Use the <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> tag for numbered lists. Each item goes inside an <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> tag.<br><br><b>Example:</b><br><code>&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;First&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Second&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</code><br><br><b>Your Task:</b> Create a numbered list with two items: 'First' and 'Second'.

To make a list, use the <code>&lt;ul&gt;</code> (unordered list) tag. Inside, each item must be wrapped in an <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> (list item) tag.<br><br><b>Example:</b><br><code>&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Apple&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Banana&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</code><br><br><b>Your Task:</b> Create a list with two items: 'HTML' and 'CSS'.
